# 2p_bot_team_sync — client A (host UI, first to connect → is_host=true
# slot 0). Runs against a `--dedicated PORT` server (mirrors the
# wan-fixes-16 production path where the "Host Server" UI spawns a
# server thread and joins as a regular client). Verifies that when
# the host clicks a bot's team chip in the lobby, the
# NET_MSG_LOBBY_BOT_TEAM wire message reaches the server, gets
# validated, mutated into the canonical lobby, and re-broadcast to
# every peer — pre-fix the click only updated the host UI's local
# lobby copy.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/dedi/2p_bot_team_sync.client_a
network connect 127.0.0.1:{{PORT}}
name HostRed

contact_sheet sheet cols 4 cell 320 180

at 30 shot t30_no_bot_yet

# Host adds a bot (Veteran tier=1). Since both clients connect before
# any tick fires (client B joins ~0.3 s after A), the bot lands at
# slot 2: client A=slot 0 (is_host), client B=slot 1, bot=slot 2.
at 40 add_bot 1
at 70 shot t70_bot_added_red

# Flip bot (slot 2) RED → BLUE. Drives net_client_send_bot_team —
# same path the lobby UI's clickable chip uses.
at 100 bot_team 2 2
at 130 shot t130_bot_blue

# Flip back BLUE → RED to verify the operation is reversible.
at 180 bot_team 2 1
at 210 shot t210_bot_red_again

at 280 end
